 <purpose>
   This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the
   representation of digital files stored on an electronic storage device or non-digital hardcopies. 
   <example>
     Paper plots of technical drawings, micro fiche, or floppy disks are
     examples of non-digital files.
   </example>
 </purpose>

 <inscope>
   <li>
     Identification of a digital file, such as a file on a computer system;
   </li>
   <li>
     Identification of a physical file, such as a stack of paper. 
   </li>
 </inscope>

